[This is not an unexpected development. As the article points out, cases have been found in 5 of the past 8 years. It seems once this disease is found, then several other cases may be found as well.

The finding will mean more quarantines, and more traces of cattle moving into and out of this herd. So others may yet be found.

More information on this disease and the association with and possible transition from elk may be found in the moderator's comments in ProMED-mail posting 20141207.3016488. - Mod.TG

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3038019,228.]
